<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Montserrat:400,700"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link href="/styles/style.css" rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <% include partials/header %>
    <h1 class="title">Home</h1>
    <article>
    <main>
      <section>
        <h2>Our Values</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Rights</li>
          <li>Civil Liberties</li>
          <li>Digital Freedoms</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Rights</h2>
        <p>
          We believe that everyone has inherent rights that must be respected and protected, regardless of their background or circumstances. These rights include, but are not limited to, the right to live with dignity, the right to freedom of expression, the right to a fair and impartial legal system, the right to equal treatment under the law, the right to privacy, and the right to access to essential services like healthcare and education. We believe that these rights are not negotiable and that they form the foundation of a just and equitable society.
        </p>
        <h3>LGBTQIA+ Rights</h3>
        <p>
          We recognize the challenges faced by lesbian, gay, bisexual,
          transgender, queer, intersex, and a-spec individuals in our society.
          We believe in equal rights and opportunities for all individuals,
          regardless of their sexual orientation or gender identity.
        </p>
        <h4>Transgender Rights</h4>
        <p>
          We recognize the challenges faced by transgender individuals in our
          society, including discrimination, violence, and limited access to
          healthcare and legal recognition. We believe that politicians must
          understand these issues and take action to address them.
        </p>
        <h3>Immigration and Asylum Seeker Rights</h3>
        <p>
          We believe in the fundamental rights of individuals to seek refuge
          from persecution and violence. We support the rights of immigrants
          and asylum seekers to fair treatment, due process, and access to
          legal representation. We also advocate for policies that promote
          the integration and inclusion of all individuals, regardless of
          their country of origin or immigration status.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Civil Liberties</h2>
        <p>
          We believe in protecting the civil liberties of all individuals,
          including freedom of speech, freedom of association, and freedom of
          the press. We oppose any government action that violates these
          fundamental rights, and we will work to promote transparency and
          accountability in government decision-making.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Digital Freedoms</h2>
        <p>
          We believe that everyone has the right to privacy and freedom of
          expression online. We oppose internet censorship and mass
          surveillance, and support policies that protect individuals' digital
          rights.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Get Involved</h2>
        <p>
          If you share our values and are interested in supporting the New UK
          Pirate Party, we welcome you to join us. You can connect with us on
          our Discord server and stay up to date with our latest news and events
          on our website.
        </p>
        <a href="/user/signup">Join Now</a>
      </section>
    </article>
    </main>
    <% include partials/footer %>
    <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
